        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 3:47PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 346 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Chickasaw State Forest, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pinson, Bemis, Beech Bluff, Madison Hall, Chickasaw State Forest,
Uptonville, Silerton, Teague, Maple Grove, Cabo, Middle Fork, East
Union, Pinson Mounds State Archaeological Park, Jacks Creek, Malesus,
Claybrook, Medon, Parkburg, Huron, and Russell Crossroads.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for west
Tennessee.</instruction>
